 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Global Head of Insider Threat State Street Jacksonville, FL 32256 Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Who we are looking for
 State Street desires to employ a program manager to oversee the Global Insider Risk Program. In this role, the incumbent will be responsible for maintaining the Global Insider Risk Program to include the development and maintenance of relevant policies, standards, training, analytical, and detection capabilities. The Insider Risk Program Manager will closely coordinate with a number of relevant stakeholders including HR, Legal, Privacy, Line fo Business leaders, Security Engineering, Fusion Center teams, and investigations teams.
 What you will be responsible for
 As the Insider Risk Program Manager you will:
 Implement key deliverables aligned with the Insider Risk Framework and program roadmap
 Develop and ensure currency of relevant Insider Risk Manage the Global Insider Risk program policies, procedures, and interaction models
 Oversee the development and deployment of insider use cases across detection platforms
 Establish relevant procedures, guidelines, and processes to risks related to insider events
 Develop and deploy insider risk training across the enterprise
 Maintain scorecards and metrics on insider incidents
 Provide advice, expertise, counsel, and support from and insider risk perspective to senior leaders as input to business decisions and medium to long term planning
 Prepare and deliver presentations to senior leadership on insider risk events, emerging trends, and relevant topics
 Ensures governance and oversight of Insider Risk program to ensure team efficiency and effectiveness and compliance to applicable State Street policies, standards, procedures, etc.
 What we value
 These skills will help you succeed in this role:
 Extensive understanding of insider risk management practices
 Thorough understanding of Advanced Persistent Threat (APT) tactics, techniques, and procedures (TTPs) to aid in response to current and future threats
 Expertise in logging and monitoring principles
 Minimum 10 years' experience in managing people, programs, and technologies
 Strong ability to react quickly and efficiently under pressure while thinking creatively
 Demonstrated experience of managing remote teams to encompass global operations
 Expert knowledge of intricacies of conducting insider and digital forensic investigations that have potential for legal action. Including but not limited to chain of custody requirements, privacy, and data security.
 Strong knowledge of technologies such as Security Incident and Event Management platforms, Entity and User Behavior Analytics platforms, Endpoint Detection and Response platforms, and Privileged Access Management platforms.
 Education & Preferred Qualifications
 10+ years of related experience
 Undergraduate degree (B.S, B.A) in Computer Science, Information Security, or related field
 Desired to have CISM, GIAC, CEH, CISSP, or other equivalent certification
